    <item>
      <title>Finite state machines in puppet</title>
      <link>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/09/28/finite-state-machines-in-puppet/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Sep 2013 06:09:08 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/09/28/finite-state-machines-in-puppet/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In my attempt to &lt;a title=&#34;setting timed events in puppet&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2012/11/14/setting-timed-events-in-puppet/&#34;&gt;push puppet to its limits&lt;/a&gt;, (for &lt;a title=&#34;recursion in puppet (for no particular reason)&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2012/11/20/recursion-in-puppet-for-no-particular-reason/&#34;&gt;no particular reason&lt;/a&gt;), to &lt;a title=&#34;Collecting duplicate resources in puppet&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/06/04/collecting-duplicate-resources-in-puppet/&#34;&gt;develop more powerful puppet modules&lt;/a&gt;, to&lt;a title=&#34;How to avoid cluster race conditions or: How to implement a distributed lock manager in puppet&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2012/08/23/how-to-avoid-cluster-race-conditions-or-how-to-implement-a-distributed-lock-manager-in-puppet/&#34;&gt; build in a distributed lock manager&lt;/a&gt;, and to &lt;a title=&#34;Dynamically including classes in puppet&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/01/16/dynamically-including-classes-in-puppet/&#34;&gt;be more dynamic&lt;/a&gt;, I&amp;rsquo;m now attempting to build a &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finite-state_machine&#34;&gt;Finite State Machine&lt;/a&gt; (FSM) in puppet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
